  "text": "Subcellular fractionation. CCRF-CEM cells (2.6 Â 10 7 /mL; 5 mL) were preincubated with 2 Amol/L trimetrexate F 0.5 mmol/L AICAr for 10 minutes and then [ 3 H]MTX was added (2 Amol/L; 0.2 ACi/mL). After 30 minutes, cells were diluted 9-fold in iced 0.9% NaCl, centrifuged at 1,000 Â g for 5 minutes, and washed once with 40-mL iced saline. Subsequent steps were done at 4jC. Cells were homogenized as described [CITATION_1] , except that hypotonic buffer at 20-fold the packed cell volume was used, and the resulting homogenate was centrifuged for 6 minutes at 1,000 Â g to yield a nuclear pellet and post-nuclear supernatant. Based on controls, >91% of cells are lysed during homogenization. The post-nuclear supernatant was centrifuged at 17,000 Â g (15 minutes) to yield a combined mitochondria-lysosome pellet. The resulting supernatant was centrifuged at 100,000 Â g (60 minutes) to yield the 100,000 Â g supernatant (cytosol). The 100,000 Â g pellet (microsomes) and combined mitochondria-lysosome pellet were each washed in isotonic buffer [CITATION_2] and recentrifuged. Pellets were solubilized and quantitated as described above. Triton X-100 was added to the cytosol to 0.3% (v/v) and 1 mL was quantitated. Subcellular distribution of [ ",
